# Reaching critical mass requires solving both sides of the market simultaneously
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Supply Side (Producers / Sellers)
  - Subsidy early adopters to seed supply liquidity
  - Provide tools that make suppliers more productive
  - Build reputation and trust signals for new entrants
  - Graduated economics: reward volume with better terms

@col:
  ## Demand Side (Consumers / Buyers)
  - Curate quality signal to reduce search friction
  - Network effect triggers: social proof, peer recommendations
  - Personalization that improves with each interaction
  - Lock-in through history, preferences, switching costs

@notes: The sequencing matters enormously. Most successful platforms seeded supply first, then drove demand. Never launch with empty shelves.

